### Test Automated Fines and Payment System Integration

### 1. Get System Settings (to see current fine rates)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admin/settings
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Get Overdue Statistics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/automated-fines/statistics
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Get Overdue Summary for Dashboard
GET http://localhost:8080/api/automated-fines/summary
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Manually Process Overdue Books
POST http://localhost:8080/api/automated-fines/process-overdue
Content-Type: application/json

### 5. Return Book in Good Condition (Legacy Method)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/borrow/return/BORROW_RECORD_ID
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Return Book with Condition Assessment
POST http://localhost:8080/api/borrow/return/BORROW_RECORD_ID/condition
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookCondition": "GOOD",
  "conditionNotes": "Book returned in excellent condition"
}

### 7. Return Damaged Book
POST http://localhost:8080/api/borrow/return/BORROW_RECORD_ID/condition
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookCondition": "DAMAGED",
  "conditionNotes": "Water damage on pages 15-20, cover slightly torn"
}

### 8. Mark Book as Lost
POST http://localhost:8080/api/borrow/mark-lost/BORROW_RECORD_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Member reported book lost during move"
}

### 9. Create Automatic Fine (determines type based on borrow record)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/fines/calculate-auto/BORROW_RECORD_ID
Content-Type: application/json

### 10. Create Lost Book Fine Manually
POST http://localhost:8080/api/fines/lost-book/BORROW_RECORD_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Book lost - replacement required"
}

### 11. Create Damaged Book Fine Manually
POST http://localhost:8080/api/fines/damaged-book/BORROW_RECORD_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "damageDescription": "Significant water damage requiring replacement"
}

### 12. Get All Fines
GET http://localhost:8080/api/fines
Content-Type: application/json

### 13. Get Member's Fines
GET http://localhost:8080/api/fines/member/MEMBER_ID
Content-Type: application/json

### 14. Get Member's Outstanding Amount
GET http://localhost:8080/api/fines/member/MEMBER_ID/outstanding
Content-Type: application/json

### 15. Record Partial Payment
POST http://localhost:8080/api/fines/FINE_ID/payment
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 5.00,
  "paymentMethod": "CASH",
  "notes": "Partial payment - member will pay remainder next week"
}

### 16. Record Full Payment
POST http://localhost:8080/api/fines/FINE_ID/payment
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 10.00,
  "paymentMethod": "CARD",
  "notes": "Full payment via credit card"
}

### 17. Mark Fine as Paid (Librarian Action)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/fines/FINE_ID/pay
Content-Type: application/json

### 18. Waive Fine
POST http://localhost:8080/api/fines/FINE_ID/waive
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "First-time offender, waived as courtesy"
}

### 19. Get Payment History for Member
GET http://localhost:8080/api/fines/payments/member/MEMBER_ID
Content-Type: application/json

### 20. Get Fine Report
GET http://localhost:8080/api/fines/report
Content-Type: application/json

### 21. Update System Settings (Fine Rates)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/admin/settings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "finePerDay": 1.50,
  "damagedBookFine": 15.00,
  "lostBookFine": 30.00,
  "updatedBy": "admin"
}

### 22. Get Unpaid Fines
GET http://localhost:8080/api/fines/unpaid
Content-Type: application/json

### 23. Get Partially Paid Fines
GET http://localhost:8080/api/fines/partially-paid
Content-Type: application/json

### 24. Create Manual Fine
POST http://localhost:8080/api/fines/manual
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "memberID": "MEMBER_ID",
  "amount": 5.00,
  "reason": "Administrative fee for special processing"
}

### 25. Get All Notifications for Member
GET http://localhost:8080/api/notifications/member/MEMBER_ID
Content-Type: application/json

### 26. Get Fine-Related Notifications
GET http://localhost:8080/api/notifications/category/FINE_NOTICE
Content-Type: application/json

### Notes for Testing:
# Replace BORROW_RECORD_ID, MEMBER_ID, and FINE_ID with actual IDs from your system
# Test in this order for best results:
# 1. Check current settings and statistics
# 2. Create some overdue scenarios
# 3. Process returns with different conditions
# 4. Test payment processing
# 5. Verify notifications are created
# 6. Check reports and statistics

### Expected Behavior:
# - Overdue books automatically generate fines
# - Damaged/lost books create appropriate fine amounts
# - Notifications are sent for each fine type
# - Payments update fine status correctly
# - Statistics reflect current system state
# - All actions are logged and auditable

### NEW ENDPOINTS - Edit and Delete Functionality

### 27. Get Fine by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/fines/FINE_ID
Content-Type: application/json

### 28. Update Fine (Edit)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/fines/FINE_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 12.50,
  "reason": "Updated fine amount - corrected calculation error"
}

### 29. Delete Fine
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/fines/FINE_ID
Content-Type: application/json

### Notes for New Endpoints:
# - GET /api/fines/{fineID}: Retrieves a specific fine by ID
# - PUT /api/fines/{fineID}: Updates fine amount and reason (only for unpaid/waived fines)
# - DELETE /api/fines/{fineID}: Deletes a fine (only if no payments recorded)
# 
# Business Rules:
# - Cannot edit fines that are PAID or PARTIALLY_PAID
# - Cannot reduce fine amount below amount already paid
# - Cannot delete fines that have payments recorded
# - Edit/Delete operations are logged for audit purposes